body:
A set of statements.

A Set of Statements

Lauren M. Hancock © 04/06/18

Retribution, poignant truths, and? Nothing to be proud, surely damned. The hell arising like a toxic poison is usurping a murky pond with ease. The water stagnant, where are the truants? The melodies from down below? Pavement warriors, keyboard soldiers, tossing back their thick god-like hair with ease, to and fro. Are they the ponies rushing forth and past, the Mustangs that some believe are a sheer must, the robust Ford utes decaled with marks of truth, the invaders from above and Above. The wretched words, the painful sighs, the disgust held within another’s eyes, as he watches what has unfolded, the tower of cards compounded, tumbling, tossed as though a moth in the clouded skies. Disguises can only hold for so long, reach out and admit before one is set to join that throng. Statements made, raw truths they grind, there is no way to turn back another’s time.

Lauren M. Hancock © 04/06/18

summary: On Friday I discovered a new artist on youtube. Her name is Chloe Moriondo, she is 15, sings and plays ukulele. Not only did she...
caption:
On Friday I discovered a new artist on youtube. Her name is Chloe Moriondo, she is 15, sings and plays ukulele. Not only did she make me discover so many new songs, but her music has been inspiring me all weekend.

When you see Chloe and listen to her music, you will instantly understand why I had to do a drawing for her. I only hope that I did her justice.
 
If you would like, you can find Chloes youtube cannel HERE
